#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:41
msgid "## How the service works"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:43
msgid "The `cron` service is run by a `crond` daemon present in memory."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:45
msgid "To check its status:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:49
msgid "``` [root] # systemctl status crond ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:52
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Tip\n"
"    If the `crond` daemon is not running, you will have to initialize it manually and/or automatically at startup. Indeed, even if tasks are scheduled, they will not be launched.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:54
msgid "Initialization of the `crond` daemon in manual:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:58
msgid "``` [root]# systemctl {status|start|restart|stop} crond ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:60
msgid "Initialization of the `crond` daemon at startup:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:64
msgid "``` [root]# systemctl enable crond ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:66
msgid "## Security"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:68
msgid ""
"In order to implement a schedule, a user must have permission to use the "
"`cron` service."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:70
msgid ""
"This permission varies according to the information contained in the files "
"below:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:73
msgid "`/etc/cron.allow`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:73
msgid "`/etc/cron.deny`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:76
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Warning\n"
"    If neither file is present, all users can use `cron`.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:78
msgid "### The `cron.allow` and `cron.deny` Files"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:80
msgid "File `/etc/cron.allow`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:82
msgid "Only users contained in this file are allowed to use `cron`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:84
msgid "If it exists and is empty, no users can use `cron`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:87
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Warning\n"
"    If `cron.allow` is present, `cron.deny` is **ignored**.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:89
msgid "File `/etc/cron.deny`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:91
msgid "Users in this file are not allowed to use `cron`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:93
msgid "If it is empty, all users can use `cron`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:95
msgid ""
"By default, `/etc/cron.deny` exists and is empty and `/etc/cron.allow` does "
"not exist."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:97
msgid "### Allowing a user"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:99
msgid "Only **user1** will be able to use `cron`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:104
msgid "``` [root]# vi /etc/cron.allow user1 ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:107
msgid "### Prohibit a user Only **user2** will not be able to use `cron`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:112
msgid "``` [root]# vi /etc/cron.deny user2 ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:114
msgid "`cron.allow` must not be present."
msgstr ""

