#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:168
msgid "## The `crontab` file"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:170
msgid "The `crontab` file is structured according to the following rules."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:176
msgid "Each line of this file corresponds to a schedule;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:176
msgid "Each line has six fields, 5 for the time and 1 for the order;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:176
msgid "Each field is separated by a space or a tab;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:176
msgid "Each line ends with a carriage return;"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:176
msgid "A `#` at the beginning of the line comments it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:182
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"```\n"
"[root]# crontab âe\n"
"10 4 1 * * /root/scripts/backup.sh\n"
"1  2 3 4 5       6\n"
"```\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:191
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Field | Description         | Detail                   |\n"
"|-------|---------------------|--------------------------|\n"
"| 1     | Minute(s)           | From 0 to 59             |\n"
"| 2     | Hour(s)             | From 0 to 23             |\n"
"| 3     | Day(s) of the month | From 1 to 31             |\n"
"| 4     | Month of the year   | From 1 to 12             |\n"
"| 5     | Day(s) of the week  | From 0 to 7 (0=7=sunday) |\n"
"| 6     | Task to execute     | Full command or script   |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:194
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! Warning\n"
"    The tasks to be executed must use absolute paths and if possible use redirects.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:196
msgid ""
"In order to simplify the notation for the definition of time, it is "
"advisable to use special symbols."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:203
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Wildcards | Description                      |\n"
"|---------------|----------------------------------|\n"
"| `*`           | All possible values of the field |\n"
"| `-`           | Indicates a range of values      |\n"
"| `,`           | Indicates a list of values       |\n"
"| `/`           | Defines a step                   |\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:207
msgid "Script executed on April 15 at 10:25 am:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:211
msgid "``` 25 10 15 04 * /root/scripts/script > /log/â¦ ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:213
msgid "Run at 11am and then at 4pm every day:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:217
msgid "``` 00 11,16 * * * /root/scripts/script > /log/â¦ ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:219
msgid "Run every hour from 11am to 4pm every day:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:223
msgid "``` 00 11-16 * * * /root/scripts/script > /log/â¦ ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:225
msgid "Run every 10 minutes during working hours:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:229
msgid "``` */10 8-17 * * 1-5 /root/scripts/script > /log/â¦ ```"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:231
msgid "For the root user, `crontab` also has some special time settings:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: docs/books/admin_guide/11-tasks.md:240
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"| Setting  | Description                   |\n"
"|----------|-------------------------------|\n"
"| @reboot  | Run command on system reboot  |\n"
"| @hourly  | Run command every hour        |\n"
"| @daily   | Runs daily just after midnight|\n"
"| @weekly  | Runs command every Sunday just after midnight    |\n"
"| @monthly | Runs command on the first day of the month just after midnight |\n"
"| @annually| Runs January 1st just after midnight |\n"
msgstr ""

